inn1.comm: outside off stump, good carry through to Ramdin as Sibanda shoulders arms
down the leg side, but clips the pad so Powell escapes a wide and a sharp take from Ramdin
cracker! full pitched just outside off stump and Sibanda misses his drive
bat on ball for the first time as this goes back down the pitch, good pace from Powell, hitting the high 80s (140kph)
ooh, good leave as this nips back a long way off the seam and goes over the top of off stump
played down into his pad, rolls onto the off side, fine opening over from Powell who bowled with real aggression

and he only lasts one ball! full inswinger from Taylor and that would have been too much for better players. Kasteni was late on it, played all around the ball and it crashed into off stump. Great start for West Indies
gets behind this with a straight bat
nearly another! Chibhabha goes fishing at an 85mph (136kph) outswinger and it almost takes the edge
Zimbabwe away with a leg-bye as he takes the thigh pad and goes down to long leg. Not sure there was a shot played at that but the umpire rules it was evasive action
loose drive and a thick outside flies down to third man through the gully, first run off the bat but not very convincing
pushes forward, ball goes past the edge and another fine over. Both new-ball bowlers are right on the money from off today, making life tough for the Zimbabwe batsmen
short and wide, Sibanda goes for the cut but fails to connect, it was there for hitting but the execution wasn't quite right

and another! shocking piece of judgment from Sibanda who completely misreads the line and shoulders arms, only to watch his off stump go backwards. Powell on fire and Zimbabwe already sinking quickly...to Powell's credit that did nip back, but it was always too close to leave. There's been a few batsmen go without playing shots so far in the World Cup
ooh! lift and bounce for Powell and pace as well. It was slightly too wide so Taylor had time to drop his hands and watch it go past
on the stumps, pushed into the on side
squared up and it takes the outside edge down to third man, Taylor opens his account but nothing has come off the middle yet
good pace from Powell, 88mph (142kph) and Chibhabha jabs into the on side and scampers a single
bat and pad into the on side, he looks an lbw candidate the way he falls across his stumps
straightens on middle and met with a solid, straight bat
way down the leg side, loose one from Taylor and very well gathered by Ramdin who has looked sharp early on with the gloves
played off the back foot, down towards back point
flashy! goes for the cut, but not enough width and the batsmen doing their best to find the edge
plays this one well, soft hands off the front foot and squeezes it past gully down to third man
pushed back into his crease and nudged into the on side
played with an angled bat, down towards backward point
Taylor plays from the crease, not much footwork and gets a big inside edge into his pads
short and wide, but again the batsman misses out as a cut shot is played without conviction
that's the area, just outside off stump and it shapes away from Taylor, whose forward push is comprehensively beaten
wide again, Taylor goes for a flashing drive and doesn't connect. Umpire Taufel stretches his arms
Taylor just loosing his line a touch, too wide again but this time no shot offered
comfortable leave this time, but a better line
played from the crease, out to cover
punched firmly to mid off
gets across his stumps and works backward of square
full, searching for the swing and it threatens to move as it takes the outside edge down to third man
drifting well down the leg side, West Indies letting themselves down despite the early wickets
back of a length, forced off the back foot off half the bat down to third man who is the busiest fielder at the moment
back to the bowler
another wide, and this will be a problem for West Indies if they don't tighten up
oh dear, again, and the bowlers really losing the plot at the moment, perhaps trying too hard after the early wickets
slightly better, but still no need to play and a long over comes to end
being forced back into the crease, plays at the top of the bounce down into the pitch
close! thick outside edge as he tries to drive off the back foot and he flies just past the outstretched hand of Dwayne Bravo at second slip...first boundary of the day
another airy drive, nearly takes the edge and played without any footwork
no shot offered, good bounce
forced off the back foot to cover
plants his front foot down the pitch and lifts the bat high
nips back off the seam, takes the top of the pad into the off side
that's a good line, close to off stump but it's a well-judged leave
slightly fuller this time, hint of away movement but well left again
doh, another loose one after a small build-up of pressure, Bennett King will be getting frustrated on the balcony
plays half forward and locates the middle of the bat down to mid
well run, defensive shots rolls into the on side and both batsmen set off straight away as square-leg couldn't do anything about it
best shot of day, foot to the pitch, free swing through the line and it races between cover and mid off
ooh, close! takes the inside edge and shoots past leg stump and away to fine leg...the perfect Chinese/French cut
that's quick and Taylor tries to glide it up and over the slips but is beaten for pace
slashes hard at this, goes in the air but falls well short of third man
again reaching around 88mph (141kph) and Chibhabha has to jab down on it
this one bounces, but it's played well as Chibhabha makes sure he uses soft hands and it drops short of second slip
pushed into the covers, an over without a wide
full, on middle, trapped between bat and pad and rolls back to the bowler...replays show it was pad first but no one appealed
that's why no one went up, he was planning on cleaning him up next ball! full and straight, Chibhabha beaten for pace and gets nowhere near it, Zimbabwe in further trouble after a promising stand
drifting onto the hips and it's glanced down to fine leg
moves away off the seam, no shot offered
solidly blocked back to the bowler
sharp bouncer, but ducks underneath without too much trouble. Good over for West Indies
squared up and bends over that one, working that down to point
rocked off the back foot behind point this time
angling into the righthander who does well enough in pressing his bat over that one into the short midwicket
oh, nearly the fourth wicket there, an inside edge off a straight ball crashing into the pitch and evading the stumps well enough
down the channel outside off, pinged on a good length and that's left alone
dibbled to cover and will they run? "No!"
short and gently arcing away from the righthander there who lets it fly through to the keeper
oh - wide delivery, seaming off the pitch, the batsman slashes at that one and a thick edge flies wide of second slip, and climbing, and that runs away very quickly indeed
fizzes through and that's left alone outside off stump with some serious shouldering of arms
the ball comes back sharply and there's a big appeal and that's going down leg, with a touch of inside edge, too
on leg and that's worked to short midwicket
short, straight and that's played down off the back foot to a very wide third man, more of a fifth man
defended into the short midwicket region again
chases that one down leg
angling in to the righthander and that's defended into the covers this time
well timed through midwicket and they come back for the second easily enough
well outside off and that's slashed away through cover
worked through leg
tempting delivery but the batsman shows good restraint and leaves that alone outside the off stump
waits patiently to tickle that one off the legs with a fine dink to long leg
late cut down to gully, an outside edge bounces just in front of the fielder
swished outside off
late cut to point
played down off the back foot to square leg
on off, a touch of away swing, and that's defended forward
decent delivery this one, the bounce surprising Matsikenyeri, who was looking to perhaps hook that one and had to settle on a defence in the end
a good length and in a good area, and that's defended stoutly into the covers
big slash at that one, looking to lamp it through point, but slices only air, carving right over the ball
left alone outside off
misdirected down leg and that's just left alone by the batsman to bring up the fifty
pops up and is fended back down
defended forward
poked down behind gully
driven forward
tucked off the legs through the on-side, a nice shot, and there's just a hint of momentum building into the Zimbabwe innings
down off
oh dear, a loose shot to a loose delivery down off - and that's a wide, in fact
left alone outside off, quiet leave that one
played off the toes to the man at short midwicket
dabbed down to gully and that would have been close for Matsikenyeri with a direct hit, but he made his ground easily in the end
played into the short midwicket region
defended down off the back foot
Taylor shuffles hopefully towards the off stick to meet the ball, but it's on a good length and he has to defend that one down in the end
regulation stuff - decent enough ball and defended down for another dot
a touch short of a good length and that's eased with a mere flick of a cover drive into the covers, obviously enough
pushed up there, straying on to middle and leg and the batsman has no difficulty in driving that in front of midwicket for an easy single
defended forward
a touch of width and that's cut - without much room for his arms, a short-arm cut if that makes sense - to point
steps down the track, but not out of his crease, and defends that one forward
the first sign of aggression from Matsikenyeri and it doesn't come off - looking to strike that over mid-on but it hardly gets up whatsoever and that's an easy catch for Daren Powell at chest height
a quiet start for Williams, working that down off the back foot into the covers
full and that's well dug out
worked into midwicket
decent delivery, a slight arc away, and that's well left by Taylor
sturdy defence, with his bat well angled down, and played on the front foot
worked down to wide third man
defended on the back foot
more back-foot defence as Williams takes his time to play himself in and get used to the conditions
driven to mid-off
plenty of width on offer from the bowler and that's played down well off the back foot with a clean, crisp cut
driven straight to the man at mid-off
steered away behind point and that's Williams off the mark. He's shown more restraint so far than he did in Zimbabwe's opener against Ireland
played into the covers
moves over to the off-side to look to straight-drive that one and ends up defending, the ball drops down. They look for a run, but decide against it
pushed out towards point
angled down to third man, actually picks the gap betweens second and fourth slip...good effort, it wasn't a big gap
pushed wide of mid off, well taken single
nicely timed, forced through the covers off the back foot with enough power for a brace
onto the front foot, very correct defensive shot out to cover
driven off the back foot square of the wicket on the off side and third man has to run round the boundary to save the four
punched out to midwicket
again midwicket into action, good diving save by Brian Lara
worked to Lara for the third time
back to the bowler
can't find any gaps, Gayle bowling quickly
out to Lara at midwicket, one of more rapid (in terms of time) maidens you will ever see
angling across the left-hander, not shot offered
punched down the pitch
glided off the back foot into the slips cordon, the man at fourth does the fielding
a rather ugly pull/swipe at that one, which cramped him for room and did him for pace...somehow managed to shovel it into the leg side
defended square to point
pushed down to third man, keeps the strike but Zimbabwe can't really press on here with four wickets already gone
tries to use his feet, nearly beaten for pace by a spinner
touch shorter, but cut straight to point
touch of bounce and turn, out to square leg
thumped into the pitch and back to Gayle on the bounce "crowd catch"
finally a run off Gayle, worked just wide of square leg
didn't turn, went in with the arm and strikes the pads but going well down leg
played from the crease, back to Collymore
on the front foot, solidly played back to the bowler
forcing drive, takes a thick inside edge through the leg side and mid on does the chasing
driven on the up, not a million miles away from Collymore but safely down to mid off
chipped into the leg side, drops short of midwicket who then throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end with a direct hit but Williams is back
bouncer, Taylor goes underneath
forced into the off side
found the gap this time, cut off the back foot through point and it's well chased down by Chanderpaul who pulls it in just short of the rope
quick and flat, into the leg side, quick single
forward defensive, back to Gayle
drifts past off stump, no shot
holds its line, tapped off the back foot back down the pitch

top shot, it goes all the way with very little effort as Taylor goes over long on with a perfectly straight bat and easily clears the ropes - first maximum of the innings - and he picked out the shortest boundary
played into the pads
slower ball, actually grips a little and goes down the leg side
comes across his stumps, works into the leg side and they set off...a direct hit from Marlon Samuels at square leg would have found Williams well short of his ground
driven off the back foot, rare misfield at cover allows them to pick up a brace although the running is again a little to close for comfort
slightly wide, Williams doesn't bother playing
pushed down to third man, good over for Zimbabwe with brought 10 runs
down the leg side, but takes the pad
arm ball, follows Williams as he tries to cut, down to short third man
into the covers
poor throw by Lara coming in from mid on, Williams would have been close to being run out again
back to Gayle
fraction short, top shot from Williams who picks the length quickly, rocks back and finds the gap at cover...this time with enough timing for a welcome boundary
worked into the leg side, easy single as midwicket runs round to square leg
cracked! another fine shot from Williams as Smith drops slightly short - although it wasn't a bad ball - and the left-hander plays another fine drive through the covers off the back foot
this backfoot drive finds the man on the fence at deep cover
takes the pad out to square leg
touch of extra bounce, comes back into Williams who plays it well out to point
good use of the wrists as he takes this from outside off stump to the left of mid on as Zimbabwe bring up their 100
full and driven down the ground to long off
can't push this into a gap, Ramdin comes round from behind the stumps
pushed to midwicket
flicked to square leg
tad shorter, off the back foot but can't find the gap
has the pressure told? not quite, Sarwan was in quickly from cover but it needed a direct hit and the extra time it took Ramdin to take the bails off means Williams is safe
defended forward
more defence, tidy, into the covers
strays on leg and that's tickled in front of square for some quick running
ambles up to the crease, sticks it just short of a good length outside off and that's dribbled out to a straightish long-off
the batsman can't get any pace on the ball and just eases it back to the bowler
down the track this time, on leg, and drives that one out to mid-on
drifted on to leg and that's worked out easily in front of square
round the wicket to the lefthander but overstretches and that goes wide down leg
neat drive, mere punch through mid-on
on middle, and that's driven out to wideish mid-on and that's the fifty partnership, well batted
a late appeal, but with both hands dangling in the air, to one which drifted in - but there was bat on there somewhere
rushed out off the pads to square
defended forward
driven out to mid-off
worked out to the covers off the back foot
poked into the covers
worked off the back foot, square
poked in front of square and that's another single, these two rotating the strike quickly and well
driven to mid-on
worked off the back foot to cover
turned round with a pull shot to square
short, width, and smashed off the back foot with a cut
on leg and that's tucked into space around midwicket
on a good length this time and the batsman can only defend forward
on leg and that's worked into midwicket
on leg and similar shot
driven to cover
on leg and that's worked again to midwicket
driven to mid-on
did well to dig that one out, getting right over it
up there and defended
driven out to mid-on this time
on the money and a tidy defence results
down leg and swept away behind square
driven to cover
outside off and that's worked into the covers
left alone outside off
on leg and that's dabbed to Lara at midwicket
on leg again and that's worked behind square
width outside off, that dies in the bounce and Williams does well to get down on to it and cut it away low
hit into the gully region this time
worked behind point
outside off and that's worked out to point
worked to midwicket
stands firm and nudges that into midwicket
plays off the back foot an uppish drive to mid-on
swept away square, they think about two but decide on just the single in the end
on leg and that's dribbled to square leg
outside off and poked down to gully this time
driven out to mid-on
worked into the on-side
taken neatly off the toes and that's worked into midwicket
down on one knee and firmly swept through square - well executed
worked into the covers this time
stands tall and nudges a single to long-on
driven to long-on
onto his back foot and pressed down, tidily
into the covers now
pushed into the covers and there's another risky single, but it's well taken in the end and even a direct hit wouldn't have had an effect this time
pops that wide of Gayle and that's the end of the bowler's spell
hit to Jerome Taylor behind point and he changes his mind about the end - throwing to the bowler's instead
worked to square and that's his fifty, a painstaking one, but well deserved, his 11th ODI fifty
driven to the covers
wide down off and the batsman slashes a cut over that one - connecting with air only
driven back to the bowler

poor calling - a mix-up, Taylor stranded mid-pitch running from the non-striker's end after the dab down to point. There was never a run there, but Taylor didn't wait for the call and set off, to his ultimate cost
and nearly strikes first ball, there's a big shout for the bowler but an inside-edge saves Chigumbura and the ball also only just misses off stump
another wide from Taylor, his sixth off a mixed day

another good shout, Chigumbura thrusts his pad down the line of the ball and it looks incredibly close but he gets the benefit of the doubt, might just have gone over the top although one of those calls that could have gone either way
another wayward one down the leg side
goes for the yorker, well dug out and well fielded by Bravo at mid off
chopped behind his legs and goes out to the vacant square leg area
cut hard and square but there's a man on the fence
inside edge into the pads, out to point
pushed to square cover
goes for the sweep, doesn't connect, through to Ramdin
fired into the legs, can't get bat onto it
driven down to mid off, good over for West Indies so far
played out to point, Williams can't get it away
unlucky! quicker ball, yorker, and it beats every and hurries down to the fine-leg rope and it's given runs which brings up a useful fifty for Williams
angling into the pads, too quick for Chigumbura
connects at last, and with the timing as it beats the man at long on and crosses the ropes...not entirely middled but it did the job
extra pace, chopped down and the ball goes behind him and bounces over the stumps
can't force this away, dropped by his feet
cut away and fine enough to beat third man into the fence so Chigumbura trying to change gear here...that's the bonus of the extra pace of Taylor, the ball goes quickly to the rope
yorker, not timed, out to mid off, no chance of a run
strangely opts not to play this
but thumps this over extra cover in no uncertain terms, one of the best shots of the day as he lifts it over the man at cover
pulled down to long on
pushed down the leg side and delicately played down to fine-leg off the face of the bat and good runnings brings them back for three, good work though from Chanderpaul on the rope
nudged to point
cut hard, through cover and to the Daren Powell on the boundary
tries to turn to the on side, gets a leading edge but it falls safe into the off side
tries to mow this through the covers, connects well but it's well stopped at cover by Samuels
quicker, shorter...Chigumbura tries to pull but gets nowhere near the ball and falls over as he swings himself off his feet...Taylor saying "drive that"
well hit...picked the slower ball and went over cover. He may not locate the middle very often but when he does it goes a long way...and he has a license in the final few overs
nearly a yorker, well dug out on leg stump
decides to go through the leg side this time, but a brilliant save from midwicket prevents any runs
worked up to long on, brilliant running by Chigumbura makes it into two...everything counts now
another good save, this time from Bravo at backward point
excellent sweep, very fine and the fielder at deep square-leg at no chance getting around...Williams playing a top innings here
tucked behind square
cuts and misses
ooh! that turned, missed the edge as Williams drives and Ramdin makes a hash of the take and it's four bonus runs for Zimbabwe as West Indies lose their way a little
starts with a good yorker, dug out into the leg side
swings and misses, goes past leg stump and another fumble by Ramdin...sloppy from West Indies
dropped...top edge from Williams and Powell did all the hard to run back from short fine-leg as the ball comes over his shoulder but he can't hold on...he so nearly had it, too
swung into the leg side
driven down the ground, good fuller ball
squeezed out behind square on the leg side and short fine-leg cleans up
heaved through the leg side and he finds the gap on the deep square-leg fence as Chigumbura continues his late charge
this one goes miles into the air but falls safely between backward point running back and deep cover running in
that was right of middle through midwicket, some power there, and more priceless runs for Zimbabwe who are giving West Indies a fight
very full, that was going nowhere
fast on full on leg stump, Chigumbura jabs down on it but all he can do is keep it out
slaps it back to Samuels on the bounce, good comeback after the early boundaries
good yorker, on off stump, straight back to the bowler
full, outside off stump, driven to backward point
pinpoint yorker, driven up the ground to long off
squeezed out, brings up the 200
low full toss, angling into the pads and it's jabbed out to cover
well, well! goes across his stumps and tries to sweep past short fine-leg but it only goes as far as the man on the edge of the circle and it's a single to finish with

inn2.comm: a loosener on leg and that's tucked away by Gayle - well, more specifically by his pad - behind square
angles that one away from the lefthander who leaves that well alone
ooh, a pretty decent ball from Mpofu, that one deviating away off the seam and Chanderpaul's caught in two minds as he offers the face of the bat
left alone outside off and that flings through to the keeper
a good line again and Chanderpaul just shoulders arms to that one
right up there, straight, and Chanderpaul defends solidly
over the wicket and that's across the lefthander, short, and he drives off the back foot
overpitches that one a touch but Chanderpaul merely drives it out to cover, still playing himself in at this early stage
decides to shoulder arms quickly to that one and that one flies through
over the wicket, by the way, to the lefthander who works that one into the leg side
crashes that one in at the legs and Chanderpaul tries to work the ball into the leg side, but doesn't get hold of it
works that one off the hips and that travels out to inside the square boundary
sprays that very wide down off
wrong length, too full, and that's driven through cover with nice timing, Chanderpaul leaning into it and sending it well on its way
another cover-drive, not quite as well timed and Matsikenyeri is excellent running round from mid-off to dive at full stretch and cut off those runs
straight and defended down off the back foot with a jump and a poke
over the wicket and pushed across the lefthander
pushed across the lefthander and goes on its way to the keeper
similar ball and that's also on its way to the keeper
short and worked into space through the covers
on a good length and driven into the covers
short and that's tucked off the hips to deep square
outside off and that's a good shot, worked off the back foot behind point but it's well cannoned back in
driven into the leg side
well waited for on the back foot and that's cut through the covers where it's well picked up on the boundary by Mpofu, running to his left
sprays that wide down off and Mpofu is annoyed with himself, audibly crying "Argh" at that one
pitches on off and that's driven slowly into the covers
angles that one across the lefthander who shoulders arms and leaves it well alone
left alone outside off, again, the batsman rising on to his back foot as he shapes to think about playing it
not forcing the batsman to play with that one which angles way across and Chanderpaul can easily leave that one alone once more
driven out to short midwicket
pushed up there and driven to cover
oh, a swing and a miss, nibbled at that one with a low cut, but misses
rushes that past the outside edge, with a hint of swing
left alone outside off
driven to mid-on
defended off the back foot
swing and a miss again with an expansive drive which would have sent the ball travelling back at the bowler had he connected at all
edged that one down behind point and Gayle is suddenly looking nervous here
false shot, there, Gayle playing over the ball and missing completely
rushes that through and, ooh, er, there's a bit of carry on to the keeper
harsh call of wide from the umpire, there, that one angling across the lefthander, but then again the umpire's qualified to make those calls
slower ball has Gayle in trouble once again, playing over it, and Mpofu flashes a broad beam of a smile at nearly getting his man
that one bends away from the lefthander on its way through to the keeper
easily left alone outside off, that one rising through
now that one really was wide - down off - and Mpofu knows it, too, remonstrating with himself
speared in straight and back of a length, Gayle coming forward to press his bat down on that one
pushed across the lefthander
oh! Jaffa has Chanderpaul prodding and is beaten all ends up, that one just failing to shave the outside edge
not timed well, just worked down into the ground off the back foot to point
played off the back foot into the covers
nice length and that's just dealt with through a defensive shot
straight and true, defended and that's a maiden over
stands up and smashes that short ball through midwicket, punished, and the pressure that was gradually building - particularly on Gayle - is immediately punctured
off the pad and Taylor does well behind the sticks to dive to his right and stop the ball - Gayle missed out there on a poor ball
off the pad again, fine, not a convincing shot and this one flies through for four leg byes
round the wicket this time and that's much better, sent down the off side channel and it's left alone
good shot! Picked off the pads and driven uppishly off the toes in front of midwicket. This is more like the Gayle we know and love/loathe depending on who you support
driven into the ground without much power and that's picked up easily
on off stump and Chanderpaul nudges that off the back foot into the cover region
angling away from the off stump and rising a touch, Chanderpaul just gets over it and defends down off the back foot into the cover region
a touch of width and poked into the covers this time
over the wicket and that's pushed across the left-hander, starting straight but jinking away naughtily
straight and full and Chanderpaul rolls his wrists over the ball, working that into midwicket
pushed up there again and that's defended forward
typical Caribbean flourish as he picks up that full ball and slams it to mid on, but straight at the fielder
this one beats the fielder...outside off stump, but Gayle doesn't care about that and disdainfully swings it past mid on with awesome power
this is more conventional, played back to the bowler
coming into the pads, Gayle tries to whip it fine but doesn't make contact and it dribbles down to fine leg...he missed out a little at that one
back and across, very solid
pushed out to cover, a very different style of game from Chanderpaul
cut away off the back foot, the crowd wants another boundary but third man keeps it to a single
back of a length, stands tall and drives this square on the off side
misses out there, short and wide but Chanderpaul doesn't time it properly, just getting the bottom of the bat on the ball
watches this sail easily past
beautifully driven, it was a floaty half-volley and Chanderpaul got his foot to the pitch and just stroked through the line...went wide of a diving mid off and raced away...classy shot
plays this at the top of the bounce, more force but less timing and straight to cover
starts well, on middle stump, and Gayle punches to mid off
ooh, that was close, angling across Gayle who tries to cut it away but is beaten by a lack of bounce and it almost takes the edge
driven, one-handed, to mid off
oversteps, the delivery is on middle and off and just offered to nip away, Gayle was squared-up a little but played it comfortably enough
full, on leg stump, and that's easy pickings for Gayle as he flicks it through square leg, and the fielder does well at fine leg to keep it to one although the running might have been sharper
full, Chanderpaul leans forward and drives to mid off
great shot, another medium-paced half-volley which Chanderpaul leans into and sends speeding between mid off and cover...that raced away and Chanderpaul looks very comfortable out there

that...has...gone...miles, what a strike from Gayle that has landed on the roof of the stand behind long on. It was full and he just swung the line and there was no doubt where that was heading...the bowler would have got neck-ache watching that one...immense

and again...massive! that's out the ground, this time with a pull as the bowler tries to pull his length back for Gayle is waiting for it and had no problems launching it high over midwicket..."Can we have out ball back, please"
that's three in a row! Is he trying to repeat Herschelle Gibbs's record. Similar to the first one, thumped high over long on and that was only heading one direction...outta here
good effort from Mupariwa, keeps his head and finds the block hole, work to cover
and another good full ball, Gayle is looking to go big but can't get underneath it
clever slower ball, Gayle was winding up but picked the change of pace and blocked it...considering the first three balls went for three that was a decent effort to finish the over
sedate start, drifts past off stump, no shot
pads this into the off side
punched to cover, a fumble but it doesn't cost any runs
another leave as Utseya fires this one through a little more
bat and pad close together, nothing doing
driven into the covers, excellent diving save and it gives Utseya a maiden to start with
driven down to long off, not timed well
on middle and leg, worked to midwicket, a much more gentle pace of the game when Shiv is on strike
rolls his wrists nicely, works into the gap at square leg with decent timing and placement, long leg cleans up
heading way down the leg side, Chanderpaul manages to get a touch on it and sends it down to long leg
driven to man sweeping on the cover fence
on leg stump, flicked to square leg, and that's drinks
round the wicket, Gayle props forward
cut away through point, there's a man on the fence to keep it to one
full and driven back to the bowler
again driven back down the pitch, well fielded by Utseya in his follow through
extra flight on that one, Chanderpaul nudges it back and Utseya fields again
lets this one go past...another tidy over from the skipper
too much width and Gayle can free his arms, slashing this through the covers and out to the sweeper
worked to midwicket, they think of a single but quickly realise it wouldn't be a good idea
gone! that came out of nowhere really, good line and length on off stump, Chanderpaul pushes at it and gets an outside edge low to the lone, wide slip where Sibanda takes a very good catch
watches his first ball go past off stump
plays at this one, comes forward and defends to point
shapes into Sarwan, bat and pad close together to end a wicket-taking over

gone! what a breakthrough, Mpofu's first ball back is just outside off stump, Gayle has a nibble and the edge flies to Taylor's left, it's a regulation catch but he tries to take it one-handed, palming it away, but Sibanda is behind him to catch the rebound...almost a replay of the one Taylor shelled against Ireland, only to be rescued by Sibanda's sharp reflexes
doh, drifting down the leg side
lets this go past
another leave, Samuels makes a watchful start
pushed to midwicket, Samuels is keen to get going but their isn't one there and a direct hit might have had him struggling
this time it's easy enough, picks the gap next to mid on
close to Sarwan, chopped into the ground
a touch wide, lets it sail to the keeper
driven on the bounce to cover
punched, without much timing, to mid off
on middle, offers to shape away off the seam, and Samuels meets it with a straight bat
probing line, Samuels opts not to play this time
nudged into the leg side, it's a well-judged run and he keeps the bowling
wide down the leg side
his bottom hand flew up off that one as the ball bounced a bit more than expected
sets himself for the back-foot push but stops on the shot
doesn't quite find the gap through cover
room outside off and that's driven into the gap at cover this time
worked off the front foot, leaning into that shot, to midwicket
worked off the front foot, leaning into that shot, to midwicket
played off the back foot into the covers
cracking drive off the front foot, a straight drive of high quality. He stays in his crease, and just watches it go
pushed right up there on a good length and the batsman does well to defend on the front foot
on-drive smacked straight to the fielder
timed off the back foot through cover, opening the blade nicely and hit right on the top of the bounce
played to the man at cover
driven through cover
short and squeezed to point
on off and that's driven to cover

oh, a straight snorter surprised Sarwan, going to hook that one, took his eyes off the ball and it crashed into the helmet, over the keeper, and onto the boundary. It's not the first time he's been hit on the head, he was struck by Dilhara Fernando in the 2003 World Cup against Sri Lanka - but he looks OK to continue here
great response from Sarwan, standing tall and that's a sweetly timed on-drive
short, on off, and that's driven through cover
up there, slightly on leg, and that's worked to leg
driven to long-on
up there again and defended on that one, forwarded
played off the back foot into the covers
strides forward and plays that off the legs in front of midwicket and that brings the hundred up
straight drive to long-off
short, wide and help yourself - only the batsman doesn't take a generous portion, slicing that up and over the man at cover and it's hunted down inside the boundary
poked down off the back foot to point
short and driven to cover
short, outside off, and that's powerfully played over cover to rocket to the boundary for a one-bounce four
defended forward, quietly

caught and bowled and Ireland gets a wicket, a soft dismissal in the end but a good catch from one which was hit quite hard and he held on. Ireland chooses not to celebrate outrageously, instead whirling his arm round, almost apologetically
punishing drive off the back foot but that's well stopped again by Matsikenyeri, who's now cut off several four-balls
round the wicket and that's darted in but Lara's off the mark with a sweet drive through cover
driven to cover
pushed forward, leaning right over to defend
worked to short midwicket
defended forward
round the wicket and that's defended into the covers
dibbled down off the back foot to wide third man
fetch that - short, and taken from off with a well-struck pull which fair rockets away in front of midwicket
stands tall and drives that one into the covers
round the wicket and that's worked into the covers
played into the covers again
comes forward defends to cover
worked up to long, easily done, rotates the strike
back to the bowler
driven to cover
bat and pad close together
angled away, short third man fields and another tidy over
driven to mid-on for an easy single
driven to mid-off this time
slower ball drifts on to leg and that's picked off the hips and turned square
straight and guided into the cover area
pitched on off and that's driven to mid-off
worked out off the back foot behind point
strides into that one and evades the sliding fielder at point, the one in the outside ring does the job
falls over in whipping that one straight to long-off, recovers, and gains a quick single
defended forward
saved very well at mid-on
this time there's an easy single to long-on
nicely driven out to deep cover
defended with one hand out to cover
driven hard, on the bounce, again to the man at cover
nice slower ball, brings a defensive shot out of Samuels who just about spots it in time
handsomely driven, free flow of the bat, but the man has been pushed back to long off so it's just the one
comes forward, head over the ball, watchful as ever
work up to long on
pushed to midwicket, they look for a single but it aint there
cut away, with a swish of the bat, but straight to point
comes down the track, doesn't middle it, but there's no danger of it carrying to long on and it's a simple single
pushed into the covers
again comfortably worked up the ground to long on
nice ball, draws Lara onto the front foot and brings an outside edge which falls just short of the very wide slip/fine gully
driven, but not really timed by Lara although he finds a gap at cover
well run, a single to mid on, where there probably shouldn't have been one
comes forward to drive, slightly lack of pace and Lara has to be careful not to spoon a catch into the covers
takes one hand off the bat this time as he locates the gap at cover, the sweeper cleans up on the fence

gone! now then, now then, a loose drive from Samuels finds point and a soft wicket for West Indies to give away. Zimbabwe continue to chip away and will feel they have sniff in this match...with that everyone takes a drink and has a moment to take stock
played off the back foot down the ground to long on
on leg stump, worked into the leg side
turned to short fine-leg
defends into the leg side and Lara calls him through for a quick single and nearly takes out Taylor as he sprints through
this one bounces a touch as Lara lets it go
comes outside off and works into the leg side, fielded by midwicket
worked off his hip, with the bounce, down to long leg
tucked to midwicket
on off stump, met with the full face of the bat and played down to long off
back of a length, outside off stump, Bravo drives off the back foot but without any timing and straight to mid off
full, under the batsmen's nose, worked to mid on
on a good length, Bravo plays with a high left elbow from the crease back to the bowler
clipped to midwicket
worked down to long on
very full on middle and Bravo can't get underneath it and finds mind on
fetch that! he middled that one, made a couple of steps down the track and met it on the full and launched it 15 rows back over long on...high and handsome
leg stump, turned to midwicket
flicked back to Williams who fields well off his own bowling
delicately played by Lara as he waits and waits for it before gliding the ball very fine past the keepers gloves, a superb dive by Chibhabha prevents the boundary
nudged into the leg side
turned to short third-man, wild throw from Sibanda and a decent effort would have caught Lara short
pushed square on the off, another slight misunderstanding but all is OK for West Indies
little bit of bounce and turn from Utseya, Lara plays it down to short third-man
easily worked out to deep midwicket
tucked off his pads to the vacant square leg area
played with strong wrists, off the back foot, to midwicket
comes down the track once pace, Williams spots him and fires it in slightly quicker...well bowled
played late by Bravo, he backs away to give himself a touch of room and guides it through short third-man...well chased
pressure-relieving boundary, Bravo rocks back as Williams drops slightly short and lifts it over the infield and out through deep midwicket
punched back to the bowler
goes for the sweep, takes a bit of bat and glove and goes almost behind him...short fine-leg cleans up
flicked down to long on...Zimbabwe need to stop the singles
played that rather late, trying another dab past the keeper, and nearly chopped it into his stumps
easily played into the midwicket area
comes forward, tidy end to the over
starts with a loose one, Zimbabwe can't afford to give away extras
back of a length, on off stump, and Lara plays out to point
chopped into the ground, picked up by Utseya at cover and Lara and sold Bravo a dummy...and direct hit at the bowler's end would have been the end for Bravo
guided to point
outside off, no shot offered, Chigumbura hit the stumps with his bowling as he came through his action
well placed from Lara, didn't try to keep it down, picked a slightly shorter ball outside off stump and up and over point and beat third man into the fence
drawn forward to that one, back to the bowler

good footwork from Bravo as he uses his crease to rock back and send this through the off side...fielded by long off who pulls a huge divot out of the ground, a good golfer would put that straight back
straight back to Utseya, takes it on shin
nudged into the leg side
cuts and misses
sweeps from outside off stump, picks out short fine-leg
nicely flighted, driven but dribbles off the inside edge into the on side
very full, but Lara manages to dig it out and times it well down to long off
Bravo surprised by a touch more bounce outside off stump and he misses his attempted cut
firmly driven back to the bowler, Bravo looks keen to finish this
walks across his stumps and whips it from about off stump through the on side and deep square-leg as to run round and pick that up...a touch of Pietersen about that
short, into Bravo's body, and he goes for the pull but it takes his shirt through to Taylor
nips back off the seam, Bravo feels he missed out and whacks his bat into the ground as the ball runs into the off side
angled down to third man

that's a classy shot, long half-volley and Bravo leans into it and just glides the ball through the covers with great timing...mid off makes a good chase and actually gets a hand on it, but slides into the rope while he still has hold of the ball
dropped into the off side, they think of a single but it's not there...the running has been iffy to say the least at times

all the way! that makes a big difference, dropped short from Mpofu and Bravo was quickly onto it and sends it high into the stands over square where it is well caught by a policeman...great hands, sir
slashes hard, superb dive at backward point prevents runs
leaves it to the keeper, good over for West Indies
short and that's a great shot worked out to inside the cover boundary and that's the fifty partnership up
dropped! That was hit really hard at Chigumbura, smashed at him, and he got a hand or two on it, more in self defence
played late off the back foot
slower ball down off and Umpire Taufel looks almost apologetic in having to give the signal
ouch, short and Bravo comes forward to try to pull that, doesn't even get his back lift up and that crashes into him at a painful height
driven short into the covers
driven straight and the man rushes round from long-on to pick that one up
short and Lara creeps over the ball, jabbing that down into the covers
wide down the off - Lara gamely reaches out to cut that one but the ball flies over the upper edge
on the money on off, a hint of awkward bounce and Lara manages to work it down off the bat, and there was a possibly a bit of glove, too
impetuous hoick there from Lara, looking to launch a wide, booming drive through the off side and that missed everything in the end
short and Lara throws his wrists into that one, crashing it out to the point boundary
short and hit clean off the back foot into the covers
angles in at the righthander and that's defended down into the covers
slants that one ever-so-slightly across the lefthander, who jabs his bat down and it crashes off the under edge and onto the floor, safe
swept off the legs behind square
dropped Oh no, how did he drop that? The crowd go wild as Bravo sends that high to third man and the ball just popped out of Gary Brent's hands as he hit the ground
defended tidily
chopped down late to third man
comes forward and stands tall, defending that on the front foot
a tidy piece of fielding at backward point, taking the non-striker's stumps with a direct hit, but the batsman was well in
another play and miss from Lara, slashing wildly with an airy cover drive, but undone by the lack of bounce on that occasion
wide of the man Sibanda at gully and Matsikenyeri does very well, once more, in the deep - he's fielded so well today
played to wide mid-on
he was going to flash and he flashed hard - and that's a wild edge that flies behind, very fine, and the ball flies up and on its way to the boundary
oh, nearly gets his man there with a prod over the ball
across Lara and he fends it down off the back foot
a sliver of width outside off and that's worked straight to the man at cover with one bounce
straight up there and that's defended with a very straight bat
lovely high backlift brought down like an inevitable guillotine with a lovely cover drive
great way to finish with a beautiful aerial drive over midwicket, these last two shots being a treat for the fans who, with the exception of Gayle, too, have had few moments of pure entertainment
